Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.31,0:00:16.74,Main,Ui,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.74,0:00:18.95,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Something in my ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.95,0:00:21.84,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Can you hear me, Yuji Itadori?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.84,0:00:22.94,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Listen and—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.45,0:00:31.63,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait, wait! I'm your ally, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.63,0:00:33.59,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Mechamaru from the Kyoto school!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.43,0:00:36.78,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.78,0:00:38.34,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Listen and understand the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.15,0:00:42.37,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Satoru Gojo has been sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.08,0:00:51.54,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Goodnight, Satoru Gojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.98,0:00:54.99,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,We'll meet again in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.99,0:00:56.66,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.66,0:00:58.99,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,But it's time for you to wake up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.26,0:01:02.24,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,How long will you keep letting it \Nhave its way with you, Suguru?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.58,0:01:23.00,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.00,0:01:24.93,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,This is a first!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.26,0:01:32.07,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Geto.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.07,0:01:34.19,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Mahito, look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.53,0:01:38.63,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,You proposed that the soul \Nexists before the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.63,0:01:41.03,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,but actually, the body is part of the soul,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.03,0:01:43.52,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,and the soul is part of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.52,0:01:45.76,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,There's no other way to \Nexplain this phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.76,0:01:51.59,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,or the fact that the body's memories flow \Ninto my brain after I swap hosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.59,0:01:54.21,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Does that really have to be a universal truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.97,0:01:58.30,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure the world doesn't operate \Ndifferently for your technique and mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.92,0:02:01.51,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,So each technique is its own world-view?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.67,0:02:05.17,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I like it. What a lovely idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.17,0:02:07.18,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.45,0:02:09.83,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to do this, hurry it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.83,0:02:12.19,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Not only is it absolutely foul, \Nbut the view here is awful, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.77,0:02:16.19,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to enjoy this \Nsight for a bit longer, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.19,0:02:19.68,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, I wouldn't want anything to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.08,0:02:21.20,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Gate, Close.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.64,0:02:46.33,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can't use this anymore, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.33,0:02:49.08,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it only holds one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.08,0:02:52.72,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Unless the man inside kills \Nhimself, it's unusable now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.72,0:02:55.03,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Huh. Lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.03,0:02:57.19,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in any case...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.46,0:03:00.60,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The sealing is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.94,0:03:02.94,Ep_Title,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 34\N{\fs30\fscy150}Pandemonium
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.50,0:03:18.01,Show_Title,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,825)\pos(320,10)\3c&H8ECEDD&}JUJUTSU KAISEN\N{\fs16\bord0\fscy100\c&HDEDCE0&}Shibuya Incident
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.67,0:04:41.00,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,We're talking about Satoru Gojo here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:44.00,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,What proof do you have \Nfor me to believe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.00,0:04:46.22,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I have nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.22,0:04:48.06,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,If I must provide something,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.06,0:04:50.01,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,it's the very fact that I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.43,0:04:52.77,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,I was killed on October 19th
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.77,0:04:56.10,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,by the special-grade \Ncursed spirit called Mahito.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.10,0:05:00.02,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,What's here is now is no more than the \Ninsurance I left when I was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.02,0:05:01.74,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Advanced insurance, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.74,0:05:03.28,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,So I had no choice but to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.28,0:05:06.66,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,set its condition for activating to \N"after Satoru Gojo has been sealed."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:09.08,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,To decrease the risk of it not going off,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.08,0:05:13.03,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,I only managed to sneak these puppets \Ninto three locations ahead of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.32,0:05:16.42,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yuji Itadori was the Jujutsu High sorcerer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:19.04,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,least likely to be leaking any information.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.57,0:05:24.48,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,And Mei Mei, given the situation, \NI'm now certain you're in the clear, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.48,0:05:25.55,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.82,0:05:30.31,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Because someone as skilled \Nat intelligence gathering as you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.31,0:05:33.55,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,was dispatched here to Meiji Shrine Station \Ninstead of acting in the shadows at Shibuya.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.55,0:05:38.67,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Itadori wasn't even a part of Jujutsu \Nsociety until several months ago, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.67,0:05:42.56,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that might have been so I'd have \Nan excuse to refuse aiding them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.56,0:05:46.08,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I'm the one who has \Nkept stopping Itadori-kun
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.08,0:05:49.29,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,from heading straight \Nto Shibuya all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.29,0:05:51.63,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we were ordered to be on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.63,0:05:52.98,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Then why...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.78,0:05:57.79,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,is a curse user currently heading \Nyour way to eliminate you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.87,0:06:10.96,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,One, two... Two, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.34,0:06:16.34,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Itadori-kun, which is stronger, these two \Nor the cursed spirit you fought earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.86,0:06:19.83,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,They're probably stronger \Nthan that grasshopper.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.47,0:06:24.81,Italics,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, the cursed spirit Itadori-kun \Nfought was able to speak human language,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.81,0:06:27.83,Italics,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,so it was semi-first-grade or higher, at least...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.83,0:06:30.96,Italics,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and things like that are \Ncrawling out of the woodwork?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.01,0:06:34.83,Italics,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder where they've been hiding \Nand what they've been up to until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.48,0:06:39.04,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Let's ignore the curse users \Nand move onward.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:41.40,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,We need to confirm Gojo-kun's status first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.40,0:06:42.78,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.11,0:06:45.83,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,The situation in Shibuya has already changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.83,0:06:49.11,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Their barrier techniques are \Nseveral degrees better than ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.11,0:06:52.87,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(339,168)\c&HD4D6D6&\3c&H000000&\bord2\shad0\fnArial\fs16}Shibuya Station
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.65,0:06:52.87,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,There are currently four \Nveils lowered over Shibuya,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.14,0:06:56.25,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,A: the veil trapping common people inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.25,0:06:59.43,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,B: the veil trapping Satoru Gojo inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.43,0:07:01.86,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,C: the veil keeping sorcerers from entering,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.16,0:07:06.86,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,and D: another veil like A to keep \Ncommon people trapped inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.86,0:07:10.79,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And you're saying the area further \Ndown these tracks is blocked by C.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.79,0:07:12.05,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.05,0:07:15.89,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,The sorcerers on standby are \Nalready inside the veil, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.89,0:07:19.13,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,And you can't use cell phones inside the veil.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.13,0:07:21.25,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like that's not all, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.25,0:07:24.75,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I can't get a hold of the assistant supervisors \Nwho are supposed to be outside the veils.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.75,0:07:27.87,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Please, just follow my directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.22,0:07:31.00,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,This insurance of mine won't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.00,0:07:32.11,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.72,0:07:34.79,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Mei-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.36,0:07:40.27,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,All right, tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.75,0:07:45.27,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Itadori, return to Meiji Shrine Station, \Nand head to Shibuya from the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.73,0:07:48.28,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Tell all the sorcerers there \Nabout Gojo being sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.82,0:07:52.03,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Get them to share our \Ngoal of recovering Gojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.03,0:07:53.03,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.38,0:07:56.38,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Mei Mei, create an opportunity \Nfor Itadori to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.38,0:07:57.77,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,After defeating the curse users,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.77,0:08:00.28,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to follow \Nthis track, for starters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.28,0:08:02.38,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know what moves \Nthe enemy will make.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.38,0:08:04.03,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,So adapt and respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.03,0:08:07.63,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, they haven't frozen \Nyour bank account yet, have they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.63,0:08:08.65,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:14.87,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,If Satoru Gojo disappears, both jujutsu \Nand human society will be upended.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.87,0:08:17.30,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but please stake your life on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.10,0:08:20.59,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,And I even thought that \Nwould be worth it once...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.89,0:08:23.31,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,I was the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:24.95,Main,Ui,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.95,0:08:26.15,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Follow whichever one you prefer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.15,0:08:27.31,Main,Ui,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Nee-sama it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.77,0:08:30.77,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, they're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.15,0:08:36.76,Main,Ebina,0000,0000,0000,,You're Mei Mei, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.95,0:08:39.95,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and do as you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.95,0:08:41.76,Main,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'll match you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.76,0:08:43.07,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.08,0:08:47.83,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial\b1\an1\fs30\bord0\shad0\pos(32,250)}21:26\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h{\fs22}Tokyo Metro, Shibuya Station\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hB5F, Shin-toshin Line Platform
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.69,0:08:47.45,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Looks like you're all awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.83,0:08:50.45,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Now, for our next...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.17,0:08:52.34,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:08:59.09,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.51,0:09:15.75,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like physical time \Nisn't passing inside here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.95,0:09:18.96,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.96,0:09:20.95,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,This is all kinds of bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.45,0:09:24.41,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it'll all work out somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.56,0:09:31.29,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:36.97,Show_Title,Eyecatch,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1350,0)\1c&H75EFED&\3c&H75EFED&\blur20\1a&HE0&\3a&HC0&\pos(320,18)}JUJUTSU KAISEN
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:36.97,Show_Title,Eyecatch,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1350,0)\1a&HFF&\3c&HC5E3EC&\pos(320,18)}JUJUTSU KAISEN
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:36.97,Show_Title,Eyecatch,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(675,0)\3c&H1EDDF0&\pos(320,18)\c&H292619&}JUJUTSU KAISEN
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.97,0:09:40.73,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,146)\fnArial\b1\bord0}21:22 Shibuya
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.73,0:09:42.64,Main,Kusakabe,0000,0000,0000,,True...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.64,0:09:45.80,Main,Kusakabe,0000,0000,0000,,Even accounting for those \Ntrapped inside the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.80,0:09:48.28,Main,Kusakabe,0000,0000,0000,,the crowd density was low.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.62,0:09:56.59,Main,Naobito,0000,0000,0000,,So the transfigured humans were \Nlying in wait inside the buildings,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.60,0:09:59.95,Main,Naobito,0000,0000,0000,,and now they've started attacking \Nthe non-sorcerers, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.95,0:10:02.96,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we've stopped \Nstanding by and started to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.62,0:10:05.59,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't much else we could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.59,0:10:08.28,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,Our response is falling too far behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.28,0:10:10.47,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,But my biggest concern is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.47,0:10:11.97,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The veil—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.47,0:10:13.93,Main,Fushiguro,0000,0000,0000,,The veil keeping sorcerers out \Nthat lowered at the same time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.52,0:10:18.21,Main,Fushiguro,0000,0000,0000,,It's been some time since \NGojo-sensei arrived at the site.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.21,0:10:20.20,Main,Fushiguro,0000,0000,0000,,Why did they choose now, of all times?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.20,0:10:22.41,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,Either something has happened inside
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.41,0:10:26.20,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,or they needed to wait for this \Nmoment as part of their strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.53,0:10:28.20,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,All I can say for certain is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:32.08,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,that these aren't the types \Nto face us without a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.49,0:10:35.21,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,I'll focus on the enemies \Nwho lowered the veils.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.21,0:10:38.64,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,You two, please rescue all \Nthe common people you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.50,0:10:48.50,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,146)\fnArial\b1\bord0}All Three Teams Enter Simultaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.43,0:10:54.40,Main,Ijichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.40,0:10:58.89,Main,Ijichi,0000,0000,0000,,Once you've confirmed the situation, \Nplease exit the veil again, Nitta-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.89,0:11:01.00,Main,Ijichi,0000,0000,0000,,With signal blocked inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.00,0:11:03.90,Main,Ijichi,0000,0000,0000,,we'll constantly need \Nsomeone on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.91,0:11:07.40,Main,Ijichi,0000,0000,0000,,I would like you to take on that role.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.73,0:11:09.58,Main,Ijichi,0000,0000,0000,,We'll do whatever it takes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.58,0:11:12.40,Main,Ijichi,0000,0000,0000,,to establish a communication network \Nusing just the assistant supervisors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.40,0:11:14.99,Main,Ijichi,0000,0000,0000,,It should be possible if we \Nmobilize those off-duty
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.99,0:11:16.41,Main,Ijichi,0000,0000,0000,,and a portion of our windo—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.11,0:11:16.41,Main,Shigemo,0000,0000,0000,,Yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.13,0:11:24.11,Main,Shigemo,0000,0000,0000,,Yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.84,0:11:29.31,Main,Shigemo,0000,0000,0000,,Yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.54,0:11:31.95,Main,Shigemo,0000,0000,0000,,Yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.30,0:11:44.47,Main,Shigemo,0000,0000,0000,,Man, bullying the weak really \Nis the best job for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.21,0:11:46.94,Main,Shigemo,0000,0000,0000,,This is what you all want, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.83,0:11:48.92,Main,Uraume,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.92,0:11:54.44,Main,Uraume,0000,0000,0000,,Please continue hunting down all \Nthe humans in suits outside the veil.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.44,0:11:55.85,Main,Shigemo,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.85,0:11:58.20,Main,Shigemo,0000,0000,0000,,And I can go inside once I'm finished, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.74,0:12:05.16,Italics,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,What's this? What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.55,0:12:07.84,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,The sealing is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.84,0:12:11.54,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,However, the Prison Realm still \Nhasn't finished processing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.54,0:12:13.98,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,all of the information that is Satoru Gojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.42,0:12:17.41,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,We won't be able to move it for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.06,0:12:28.18,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,They got one over on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.62,0:12:31.54,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Itadori, good news!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.54,0:12:32.19,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.19,0:12:35.91,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}They can't move Gojo from \Nwhere he was sealed on floor B5.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.19,0:12:38.44,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\an3\fnArial\bord0\shad0\b1\pos(611,302)}21:27 Between Meiji Shrine and Shibuya Stations
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.91,0:12:36.68,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Why not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.68,0:12:38.44,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Because he's Satoru Gojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.12,0:12:40.25,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Makes sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.25,0:12:41.95,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Let's encircle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.95,0:12:44.10,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have sorcerers follow the subway lines
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.10,0:12:46.45,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,into Shibuya Station from \Neach neighboring station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.45,0:12:49.96,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\bord4\shad0\fnArial\fs18\c&H31312F&\3c&HF8F4EC&\fscx93\pos(227,27)}Shin-toshin Line \NMeiji Jingu Station
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.45,0:12:49.96,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\bord4\fscx80\shad0\fnArial\fs18\c&H31312F&\3c&HF8F4EC&\pos(477,58)}Fukubumon Line \NOmotesando Station
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.45,0:12:49.96,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\bord4\fscx80\shad0\fnArial\fs18\c&H31312F&\3c&HF8F4EC&\pos(491,174)}Seiyoko Line \NDaikanyama Station
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.45,0:12:49.96,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\bord4\fscx85\shad0\fnArial\fs18\c&H31312F&\3c&HF8F4EC&\pos(183,288)}Den-en-toshin Line \NIkejiri-ohashi Station
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.45,0:12:49.96,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial\bord2\shad0\b1\3c&H31312F&\c&HF8F4EC&\pos(322,158)}Shibuya Station
Dialogue: 1,0:12:46.79,0:12:49.96,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Then, once the veil keeping sorcerers \Nout is lifted, we charge in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.96,0:12:53.64,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Have them follow them? \NBut I can't get a hold of Ijichi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.64,0:12:54.80,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.80,0:12:55.96,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.39,0:12:59.03,Flashback,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, who was sent to Shibuya?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.03,0:13:01.34,Flashback,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.40,0:13:15.48,Main,Transfigured,0000,0000,0000,,Kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.88,0:13:45.18,Main,Transfigured,0000,0000,0000,,D-D-D-Did you call for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.92,0:14:18.92,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Nanamin!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.92,0:14:24.43,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Nanamin!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.92,0:14:25.85,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Nanamin, are you here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.85,0:14:29.48,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Nanamin, are you here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.99,0:14:28.89,Main,Fushiguro,0000,0000,0000,,Itadori?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.48,0:14:31.15,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nanamin?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.15,0:14:34.56,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Gojo-sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.19,0:14:39.69,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,has been sealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.69,0:14:43.88,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,...has been sealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.68,0:14:42.85,Main,Fushiguro,0000,0000,0000,,Sealed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.85,0:14:45.16,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,You two, change of plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.16,0:14:47.46,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,We meet up with Itadori-kun at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.88,0:14:49.71,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,If it's true that he's been sealed,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.71,0:14:50.98,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,then it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.98,0:14:53.34,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,For every human in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.74,0:14:57.98,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Man, now they know what we're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.98,0:15:00.55,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,The sorcerers are going to \Ncome here in force now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.55,0:15:04.04,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be staying behind. \NWhat about the rest of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.25,0:15:06.18,Main,Choso,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting revenge for my younger brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.18,0:15:09.19,Main,Choso,0000,0000,0000,,and killing Yuji Itadori and Nobara Kugisaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.19,0:15:14.07,Main,Choso,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll go get the rest of my brothers from \Nwhere they're being kept in Jujutsu High.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.07,0:15:17.48,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about this Kugisaki, \Nbut you can't kill Itadori.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.48,0:15:18.90,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,We're turning him into Sukuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.90,0:15:20.21,Main,Choso,0000,0000,0000,,Not my problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.94,0:15:26.11,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Jogo, calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.78,0:15:32.47,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I think I want to kill Itadori, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.47,0:15:34.90,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,Mahito! What are you—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.90,0:15:38.29,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,From what I could tell after \Nseeing Satoru Gojo in person,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.29,0:15:42.30,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,now that he's sealed away, the sorcerers \Nand cursed spirits are evenly matched.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.30,0:15:45.16,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,If Sukuna is resurrected, \Nwe'll have a huge advantage,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.16,0:15:47.12,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,and victory is basically ours, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.12,0:15:48.80,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.80,0:15:49.89,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,But then,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.89,0:15:53.31,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,that also means we're perfectly capable of \Nwinning with the forces we have now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.12,0:15:56.28,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,So let's kill Itadori!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.28,0:15:57.65,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.65,0:16:00.99,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we lose Sukuna, we can still win.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.32,0:16:02.36,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.36,0:16:04.61,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,As serious as can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.36,0:16:18.37,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need to be the one smiling \Nin the wasteland a century from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.73,0:16:22.41,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,As long as curses can live as people, \Nthat's all that matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.63,0:16:27.28,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,Sukuna isn't our ally.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.28,0:16:31.88,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,We might even be the ones facing \Ngreater risk if he is resurrected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.88,0:16:36.40,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,But if Sukuna is resurrected, that's \Nguaranteed to usher in the age of curses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.40,0:16:39.39,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,We are not like the humans of today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.39,0:16:41.08,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,We do not fear death,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.08,0:16:43.89,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,and we follow the path to \Nour goals without falsehoods.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.89,0:16:47.74,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,That is the essence of us curses \Nthat those fakes lack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.74,0:16:48.82,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.82,0:16:49.66,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,Wha?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.66,0:16:52.50,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how off-kilter or inconsistent,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.50,0:16:56.05,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,we always act in accordance \Nwith our true desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.05,0:16:58.16,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it means to be a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:02.47,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, when I said you were wrong,\NI meant regarding what curses are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.47,0:17:04.80,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,I agree, the whole resurrection \Nthing is one possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.80,0:17:06.97,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Nor do I really want to fight you over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.97,0:17:09.67,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,So how about we play a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.93,0:17:13.86,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,If I run into Itadori first, I'll kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.35,0:17:18.33,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,If you find him first, you can give him the \Nfingers and let Sukuna regain his power.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.68,0:17:21.78,Main,Choso,0000,0000,0000,,And if I find him first, I kill him. That okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.78,0:17:22.62,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.62,0:17:25.01,Main,Mahiro,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You want in, too, Choso?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.01,0:17:26.36,Main,Mahiro,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.81,0:17:29.52,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,You're more on Jogo's side \Nif you had to pick, right, Geto?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:30.80,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.80,0:17:33.94,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I have to stay here and watch \Nover the Prison Realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.94,0:17:35.81,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll abstain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.47,0:17:39.41,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Do whatever you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.41,0:17:41.20,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,As far as I'm concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.20,0:17:44.44,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Sukuna was just the alternative \Nif the Prison Realm failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.44,0:17:46.38,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,This is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.38,0:17:50.89,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,All the sorcerers, even Itadori, \Nwill be heading this way to save Gojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.89,0:17:53.00,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,So all you have to do is wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.00,0:17:54.59,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,This won't even be a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.54,0:17:55.66,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Ready, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.50,0:17:59.36,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,Wha—Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.48,0:18:04.85,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Those cursed spirits are \Nsmarter than you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.16,0:18:06.27,Main,Nanako,0000,0000,0000,,Give him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.86,0:18:15.64,Main,Mimiko,0000,0000,0000,,We cooperated with you and \Nkept dropping monkeys for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.64,0:18:18.74,Main,Nanako,0000,0000,0000,,Now give us back Geto-sama's \Nbody like you promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.74,0:18:21.01,Main,Mimiko,0000,0000,0000,,Don't toy with...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.01,0:18:23.24,Main,Nanako,0000,0000,0000,,...Geto-sama any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.50,0:18:25.87,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously, I'm not giving him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.87,0:18:29.87,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I don't recall leaving your heads empty, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.87,0:18:32.16,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Next time you make a promise with a sorcerer,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.16,0:18:35.13,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,you should make it clear that it's a pact.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.13,0:18:36.24,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Now, begone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.24,0:18:39.22,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you want to be killed by this body?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.96,0:18:43.58,Main,Nanako,0000,0000,0000,,You'll regret this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.30,0:18:47.13,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Regret, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.73,0:18:48.74,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.74,0:18:51.88,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,How did that taste again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.90,0:18:56.74,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Nanamin!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.91,0:18:56.74,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Nanamin!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.74,0:18:59.74,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Na-na-min! Na-na-min!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:03.35,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Na-na-na-na-na-na-min!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.35,0:19:04.31,Main,Fushiguro,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.99,0:19:06.75,Main,Fushiguro,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.16,0:19:08.75,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Na-na—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.75,0:19:10.92,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Fushiguro! Nanamin!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.92,0:19:12.11,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,And... who?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.11,0:19:15.76,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,You really were referring to \NNanami-san with that "Nanamin," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.13,0:19:17.41,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,Geto-san did?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.01,0:19:22.95,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,To be more precise, the thing \Nthat's living within Suguru Geto.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.95,0:19:25.92,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,The inside of Shibuya Station \Nis currently a real Pandemonium.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.92,0:19:28.55,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's full of those special-grades, \Nthe cursed spirits they brought with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.55,0:19:30.73,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,the curse users tied to Geto,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.73,0:19:33.52,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,as well as transfigured humans \Nand normal people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.52,0:19:36.09,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, it would be \Nfaster to attack through
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.09,0:19:38.04,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,the subway from the neighboring stations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.04,0:19:41.52,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,But in order to do that, \Nwe need to lift that veil first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.52,0:19:43.32,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.32,0:19:45.04,Italics,Mechamaru,0000,0000,0000,,Please multi-task.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.47,0:19:48.04,Italics,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,I guess this isn't the time for complaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.37,0:19:51.44,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,There are several requests only \Na first-grade can fulfill.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.44,0:19:55.41,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,I'll step outside and take care \Nof all those with Ijichi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.88,0:19:58.25,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,During that time, I want \Nyou three to do something
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.25,0:20:00.05,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,about the veil keeping sorcerers out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.26,0:20:01.24,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,Ino-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.92,0:20:04.91,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,Kusakabe-san and Zen'in's special first-grade
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.91,0:20:07.60,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,sorcerer should be inside this veil, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.60,0:20:09.23,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,If you're able to meet up with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.23,0:20:12.56,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,please tell them about the situation \Nand request their help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.56,0:20:15.48,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,I think they already understand the situation, \Nthough, thanks to that shouting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.48,0:20:16.52,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,Roger that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.76,0:20:21.00,Main,Nanami,0000,0000,0000,,Also, please take care of these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.94,0:20:23.50,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.11,0:20:27.56,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Ino-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.56,0:20:30.54,Italics,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,Nanami-san is counting on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.54,0:20:32.24,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,You two!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.60,0:20:35.76,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,Before we start the mission, \Nlet me make it clear how important this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.76,0:20:39.91,Main,Our topic,0000,0000,0000,,The two main issues with losing Gojo-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.91,0:20:42.66,Main,Our topic,0000,0000,0000,,First, the collapse of the Gojo clan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.66,0:20:45.16,Main,Our topic,0000,0000,0000,,The Gojo clan is currently a one-man \Nteam of Satoru Gojo himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.16,0:20:48.07,Main,Our topic,0000,0000,0000,,There are also lots of \Nsorcerers who have been saved
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.07,0:20:50.52,Main,Our topic,0000,0000,0000,,due to Gojo-san's influence, pride, and whims.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.12,0:20:50.52,Sign_Basic,Our topic,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\move(320,-34,320,164)\fnTimes New Roman\bord0\shad0\b1\c&H000000&}Throughout Heaven and Earth, I Alone Am the Honored One
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:53.52,Main,Our topic,0000,0000,0000,,Itadori, you're one of those sorcerers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.52,0:20:54.16,Main,Yuji,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.16,0:20:55.40,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,So casual about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.77,0:20:59.24,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,All of those people are going to \Nfind themselves in trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.24,0:21:01.16,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,and, worst case, eliminated!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.16,0:21:05.58,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,That brings us to issue two: \Nthe collapse of the power balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.58,0:21:07.41,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,All of the cursed spirits \Nand curse users who've
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.41,0:21:09.32,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,been keeping quiet because \NSatoru Gojo was around
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.32,0:21:11.41,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,will start taking action all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.41,0:21:14.20,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if those guys from \Nissue two try starting a war
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.20,0:21:17.16,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,while society's in disarray \Nfrom fighting over issue one,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.16,0:21:18.42,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,we'll lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.97,0:21:21.13,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,That's the future as Nanami-san and I see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.13,0:21:22.92,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,So what do you think happens if we lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.92,0:21:27.68,Main,Fushiguro,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, the age of humans \Nwould probably be over for Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.68,0:21:29.69,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,See, you get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.28,0:21:32.19,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's go, you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.54,0:21:36.04,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,We'll break that veil before \NNanami-san gets back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.94,0:21:39.28,Main,Ino,0000,0000,0000,,Let's rescue Satoru Gojo!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.20,0:23:13.82,Main,Ogami,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that, Awasaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.82,0:23:16.32,Main,Ogami,0000,0000,0000,,"Satoru Gojo has been sealed."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.32,0:23:19.25,Main,Ogami,0000,0000,0000,,They're leaking information \Nto their enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.77,0:23:22.11,Main,Awasaka,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with that, Old Ogami?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.11,0:23:24.84,Main,Awasaka,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally starting to feel real to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.84,0:23:28.47,Main,Awasaka,0000,0000,0000,,Satoru Gojo really has been sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.47,0:23:30.84,Main,Awasaka,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.84,0:23:34.67,Main,Awasaka,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's going to \Nhappen to this country now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.36,0:23:36.92,Main,Ogami,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing new.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.92,0:23:39.85,Main,Ogami,0000,0000,0000,,People will curse, be cursed, and die.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.14,0:23:42.08,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,Madam, did you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.08,0:23:45.22,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,They said the Gojos' little \NSatoru-kun was sealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.22,0:23:45.95,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.95,0:23:47.69,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,I always thought that would \Nhappen to that boy one day!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.69,0:23:49.32,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,He was always flaunting his style,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.32,0:23:50.94,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,acting like he was nothing \Nbut leg below his nipples!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.94,0:23:52.13,Main,Jogo,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Seance"!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.99,0:23:54.87,Next_Ep_Title,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HFFFFFF&\bord2\blur4}Next Episode\N{\fs30\fscy150}Seance
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.13,0:23:54.97,Main,Mahito,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Geto-san, did you hear? The Gojos' little—

